"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-remco-evenepoel-olympic-road-race-result-paris-b2590714.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  A week after winning the Olympic time trial and only two weeks after finishing on the podium of the Tour de France, the brilliant Belgian destroyed the field - and his rear tyre - en route to an historic second gold  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 316, \"end\": 330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999999998026396, \"rank\": 1.901704864871398e-10, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 346, \"end\": 353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9972631080383573, \"rank\": 0.0027443718547404163, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Remco Evenepoelwon a thrilling and chaoticOlympicroad race on the streets of Paris to complete afamous double after claiming goldin the time trial a week ago.\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 721, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 640, \"end\": 645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.3242578563759455e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A week before that, he was standing on the podium of the Tour de France.\", \"from\": 722, \"to\": 794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 779, \"end\": 793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999999998026396, \"rank\": 1.901704864871398e-10, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those three things should not be possible by one rider in one summer, but Evenepoel is exceptional.\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 894, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With 30km to go, the Belgian decided he'd had enough of waiting and blasted off into the distance leaving world-class riders including his main rival, Mathieu van der Poel, behind.\", \"from\": 896, \"to\": 1076, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 917, \"end\": 924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9972631080383573, \"rank\": 0.0027443718547404163, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He sped up to the breakaway leaders and rode through them, dropping them one by one as tried in vain to cling on to his wheel.\", \"from\": 1077, \"to\": 1203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It had been a tactical road race; Evenepoel turned it into a 45-minute time-trial, knowing no one could live with him.\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1322, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There was some late drama when his rear tyre punctured with 3km to go.\", \"from\": 1324, \"to\": 1394, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In an incredible scene, Evenepoel stood on a narrow road next to his busted bike, surrounded by thick waves of fans while he screamed at a mechanic in the distance to hurry up and bring him a new one.\", \"from\": 1395, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After what seemed like an eternity, finally it arrived, and he got the message that his lead was still a healthy minute.\", \"from\": 1596, \"to\": 1716, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When he reached the finish line he hopped off his bike and threw his arms out wide.\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1801, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Standing under the Eiffel Tower, it will be one of the iconic images that endures long after his remarkable career is over.\", \"from\": 1802, \"to\": 1925, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a symbol of his dominance; the Eiffel Tower could have laid down on its side and still not touched his nearest rival.\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 2050, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Behind him, France secured an unlikely double in Valentin Madouas and Christophe Laporte.\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2064, \"end\": 2070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9767478196709908, \"rank\": 0.015283013564636294, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2101, \"end\": 2117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Valentin Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}, {\"begin\": 2122, \"end\": 2140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christophe Laporte\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Madouas, the French national road race champion, had clung on gamely as Evenepoel obliterated the field and he was the last rider to be dropped, with 15km remaining of the Montmartre circuit that staged the finale of the race.\", \"from\": 2142, \"to\": 2368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2142, \"end\": 2149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}, {\"begin\": 2155, \"end\": 2189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_National_Road_Race_Championships\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French national road race champion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_National_Road_Race_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_National_Road_Race_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 2314, \"end\": 2324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1646832038701217e-14, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom Pidcock, who won mountain bike gold for Britain this week, finished 13th, crossing the line alongside the world champion Van der Poel.\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2369, \"end\": 2380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Pidcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\"}, {\"begin\": 2413, \"end\": 2420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9920694883629144, \"rank\": 0.007992525094788615, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No one could live with Evenepoel.\", \"from\": 2509, \"to\": 2542, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Aged 24, he has already won one of cycling's three grand tours, the Vuelta a Espana, and stages at all three.\", \"from\": 2543, \"to\": 2652, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He has won world titles in the road race (2022) and the time trial (2023).\", \"from\": 2653, \"to\": 2727, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He has won two of cycling's five monument races and it is not unfathomable that he might one day complete the set, something only three riders have ever done.\", \"from\": 2728, \"to\": 2886, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of those is the great Eddy Merckx, the fellow Belgian Evenepoel is so often compared to, and with good reason.\", \"from\": 2887, \"to\": 3001, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2913, \"end\": 2924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddy_Merckx\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.1961734779814565e-65, \"text\": \"Eddy Merckx\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddy_Merckx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddy_Merckx\"}, {\"begin\": 2937, \"end\": 2944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9972631080383573, \"rank\": 0.0027443718547404163, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"1.\", \"from\": 3003, \"to\": 3005, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Remco Evenepoel (Belgium) 6:19:34 2.\", \"from\": 3006, \"to\": 3042, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3006, \"end\": 3021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Remco Evenepoel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\"}, {\"begin\": 3023, \"end\":